title: ScanSAR Wide beam product
description: The ScanSAR Wide (SCW) product is a georeferenced ground coordinate multi-look imageproduced by multiplexing four single beams for both SWA and SWB. Image pixels are 50m square and scenes are nominally 450 km for SWB and 500 km for SWA in the cross track (range) dimension. The along track (azimuth) scene dimension is user selectable. SCW products are generated using four looks in range and two looks in azimuth for a nominal total of eight looks.
